Data Protection Information Sheet for TeamViewer Customers
Version as of July 17th, 2023
This Data Protection Information Sheet provides an overview of how TeamViewer Germany GmbH, Bahnhofsplatz 2, 73033 Göppingen, Germany (hereinafter “TeamViewer” or “we”) collects and processes personal data of its customers.
Processing as Processor.
When you use TeamViewer software and services as a customer (hereinafter “Customer” or “you”) and you are not a natural person, using the software or services in a purely personal or family activity (cf. Art. 2(2)(c) EU General Data Protection Regulation, “GDPR”), TeamViewer processes personal data in the meaning of Art. 4 GDPR and acts as Processor, whereas you act as Controller (Art. 28 GDPR). In the following, in addition to our
TeamViewer DPA
and related
annexes
, as amended from time to time, we summarize what personal data we collect, process or use and what rights data subjects are entitled to in connection with the use of our software and services.
Processing as Controller.
In addition, we process personal data as “controller” under the GDPR when providing our software and services. Information on such processing activities in accordance with Art. 13, 14 GDPR can be found in our
Privacy Notice for TeamViewer Products
.
Information on data processing.
In connection with the use of TeamViewer software and services, we perform the processing activities described in
Annex 1
to our DPA, as amended from time to time. In connection with these processing activities, we use subcontractors, as set forth in
Annex 3
to our DPA, as amended from time to time.
Technical and organizational measures.
When processing personal data, TeamViewer complies with Art. 32 GDPR and implements appropriate technical and organizational measures to ensure a level of security appropriate to the risk, taking into account the state of the art, the costs of implementation and the nature, scope, context and purposes of the processing as well as the risk of varying likelihood and severity for the rights and freedoms of natural persons. The measures adopted are specified in TeamViewer’s overview of technical and organizational measures (TOMs,
Annex 2
to our DPA), as amen-ded from time to time.
Security of processing.
Taking into account the type of processing and the personal data available to TeamViewer, TeamViewer supports the Customer with appropriate technical and organizational measures to comply with Art. 32 – 36 GDPR, in particular with regard to the security of processing, notification of a personal data breach to the supervisory authority, communication of a personal data breach to the data subject, data protection impact assessments as well as the consultation with supervisory authorities.
Data protection by design and by default.
Information on how TeamViewer protects personal data by design and by default can be found in TeamViewer’s overview of technical and organizational measures (Section 6 in our TOMs,
Annex 2
to the DPA).
Assistance to the Customer in the execution of requests of data subjects.
TeamViewer assists the Customer with appropriate technical and organizational measures in the execution of requests to exercise the rights of data subjects. If a data subject contacts us directly to exercise his or her rights pursuant to Art. 12 et. seq. GDPR, we will immediately forward this request to the Customer.
Rights of data subjects towards TeamViewer.
Under the conditions set forth therein, the GDPR grants data subjects the following rights, which the data subject may exercise towards TeamViewer as described in the
Privacy Notice for TeamViewer Products
:
Right of access (Art. 15 GDPR);
Right to rectification (Art. 16 GDPR);
Right to erasure (Art. 17 GDPR);
Right to restriction of processing (Art. 18 GDPR);
Right to data portability (Art. 20 GDPR);
Right to object (Art. 21 GDPR).
In addition, we inform data subjects in accordance with Art. 13 and 14 GDPR when we obtain personal data from them or from another source.
Data subjects may assert their rights by e-mail to privacy@teamviewer.com, via a support ticket or in writing to TeamViewer Germany GmbH, Bahnhofsplatz 2, 73033 Göppingen, Germany.
Data protection officer.
TeamViewer has appointed an external data protection officer who can be contacted at privacy@teamviewer.com. You are also free to contact the relevant data protection authority, Der Landesbeauftragte für den Datenschutz und die Informationsfreiheit Baden-Württemberg, Lautenschlagerstraße 20, 70173 Stuttgart, Germany.
Further Information on security measures and certificates.
Further information on security and data protection measures and our certificates of TeamViewer and its partners (e.g., ISO 9001, SOC2, SOC3, HIPPA/HITECH and ISO 27001) can be found in the TeamViewer
Trust Center
.
